{"cursor":"3078","size":15,"audio":[],"currentlang":"en","article":"{{Infobox Muslim scholar |notability = Muslim scholar |era = |image = |caption =\n|name = 'Al-Sakhawi' |title = Al-Hafiz, Shams al-Din |birth_date = 1428 CE (831\nAH) Cairo, Egypt |death_date = 1497 CE (902 AH) Medina |region = Middle\nEastern Scholar |Maddhab = Shafi'i |school_tradition = Sunni\n| main_interests = Hadith, History\n|influences = Ibn Hajar al-Asqalani |influenced = }}\n\n'Shams al-Din Muhammad ibn `Abd al-Rahman al-Sakhawi' (, 1428/831 AH - 1497/902\nAH) was a reputable Shafi'i Muslim hadith scholar and historian who was born in\nCairo. \"Al-Sakhawi\" refers to the village of Sakha in Egypt, where his relatives\nbelonged. He was a prolific writer that excelled in the knowledge of [[hadith]],\n[[tafsir]], literature, and history. His proficience in hadith has its\ninfluences trace back heavily on his Shaykh Al-Hafiz Ibn Hajar al-Asqalani. He\ndied in Medina.\n","linknr":109,"url":"Al-Sakhawi","recorded":1375069375,"links":["/w/index.php?title=Al-Sakhawi&action=edit","/w/index.php?title=Al-Sakhawi&action=edit","//bits.wikimedia.org/favicon/wikipedia.ico","/w/opensearch_desc.php","//en.wikipedia.org/w/api.php?action=rsd","//creativecommons.org/licenses/by-sa/3.0/","/w/index.php?title=Special:RecentChanges&feed=atom","//bits.wikimedia.org/en.wikipedia.org/load.php?debug=false&lang=en&modules=ext.gadget.DRN-wizard%2CReferenceTooltips%2Ccharinsert%2Cteahouse%7Cext.rtlcite%2Cwikihiero%7Cext.uls.nojs%7Cmediawiki.legacy.commonPrint%2Cshared%7Cmw.PopUpMediaTransform%7Cskins.vector&only=styles&skin=vector&*","//bits.wikimedia.org/en.wikipedia.org/load.php?debug=false&lang=en&modules=site&only=styles&skin=vector&*","//bits.wikimedia.org/en.wikipedia.org/load.php?debug=false&lang=en&modules=startup&only=scripts&skin=vector&*","//bits.wikimedia.org/geoiplookup","//meta.wikimedia.org","#mw-navigation","#p-search","/wiki/Muslim","/wiki/Scholar","/wiki/Hijri_year","/wiki/Cairo","/wiki/Egypt","/wiki/M